      "content": "it feels like more than just a moment of letting go. like, even if i stop being the fixer, the debt is still there. the expectations, the lost years, the emptiness... it doesn't just go away because i take a break. it’s like i’m trapped in a room that’s slowly filling with water, and i’ve already tried every single way to swim to the surface. i'm just so weary of the struggle. does peace even exist if everything feels this heavy?",
